II.  For the conference component 

While the Event Managers will do the bulk of the work, there is an expectation that 
LKYSPP will make available time of staff members to plan for the conference. The work 
of these LKY staff will center on the following: 

(i)  Plan conference content and help design the conference; 
(ii)  Work on any background documents for the conference; 
(iii) Help prepare the communication strategy for the conference; 
(iv) Work with the event manager(s) to market the conference to relevant stakeholders 
inside and outside and Singapore; 
(v)  Prepare a conference dissemination strategy, including helping set up a conference 
website; 
(vi) Work  on  compiling  the  conference  proceedings,  including  peer  review  of  final 
proceedings. 

Those  LKYSPP  staff  members  involved  in  the  conference  planning  will  also  help 
facilitate the management of the conference for the 1.5 days, and help ensure that all 
relevant issues are taken care of. 

III.  For the executive training component 

Relevant staff of the Executive Unit of the LKYSPP will be involved in designing and 
implementing  the  executive  training  on  subnational  financing.  This  will  consist  of 
designing the module, managing the logistics and administrative aspects of the training 
itself (including carrying out the satisfaction survey of participants), and providing the 
training. In particular, LKYSPP involved in the training component will be responsible for: 

(i)  Designing  the  Executive  Education  module,  incorporating  ADB  feedback  in  its 
design; 
(ii)  Marketing the module to DMCs; 
(iii) Managing all logistics of participants to the training; 
(iv) Carrying out a pre-event, and a post-event, state of learning of the participants on 
sub-national financing; 
(v)  Managing the training program for the duration that it is on offer; 
(vi) Preparing a report that documents the lessons of the training component of the TA; 
(vii) Working with ADB to continue, or even scale up, the training to DMC officials.
